<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n05fcvf"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n05" href="#n05fcvf">N05 (VI.B.2)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n05all.htm#n05fcvf">front cover verso(f)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> moving spirit</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">He <font color="green">[Edward Bunting]</font> lodged with and became fast friends of the McCrackens, whose love for Irish folk music as well as the influence of Dr. James MacDonnell, the <mark>moving spirit</mark> in the Belfast Harper&apos;s Festival of 1792, drew him into that collection, study and arrangement of old Irish music which for the next fifty years absorbed all the time he had to spare from his duties as a professional musician. <small> Alfred Perceval Graves, <a name="ILMS" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#ILMS"><cite title="source">Irish Literary and Musical Studies</cite></a>, (1913) (Edward Bunting) 192</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
